                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="228.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Visual storytelling is the art of communicating a narrative through images. Whether it's a comic strip, a children's book illustration, a character concept, or a single dramatic scene, every picture has the potential to tell a story. In this chapter, students will explore how illustration can express ideas, emotions, and action without words—or in combination with them. By understanding key elements such as character, setting, expression, and sequence, young artists will learn how to bring stories to life visually." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <JFXButton fx:id="nextButton" buttonType="RAISED" layoutX="581.0" layoutY="2150.0" onAction="#finishButtonHandler" prefHeight="38.0" prefWidth="202.0" style="-fx-text-fill: white; -fx-background-radius: 25; -fx-background-color: #42736c;" text="Finish" textFill="#42736c">
