                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="1106.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Body Language" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="1137.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Backgrounds can be detailed or simple depending on the style, but they should always support the story. A detailed cityscape suggests a fast-paced world, while an empty field can evoke loneliness or peace. Backgrounds should not distract from the subject, but rather complement it." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="1218.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Mood and Atmosphere" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="1251.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="The environment also helps set the mood. Warm colors like red, orange, and yellow create feelings of energy, heat, or happiness. Cool colors like blue and purple create calm, mystery, or sadness. Fog, lighting, shadows, and textures also influence the atmosphere." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="1329.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Worldbuilding" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="1365.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="In fantasy or sci-fi illustrations, worldbuilding means designing unique cultures, architecture, clothing, and landscapes. These details make a story world believable and immersive. For example, a flying city with glowing towers gives a completely different feeling than a swamp village made of bones and vines." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="1620.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Panels are used in comics and storyboards to break a story into scenes or moments. The size and shape of panels can control pacing. Small panels can show quick action; large panels slow things down and emphasize key scenes. Learning how to arrange panels is essential for comic artists and animators." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="1698.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Timing and Movement" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="55.0" layoutY="1730.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Illustrators suggest time passing by repeating characters in different positions, using motion lines, or showing effects like wind or light. For example, a character shown mid-jump, with their scarf trailing behind, suggests action and speed. Showing what happens before and after helps build story arcs within the image." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
